# NestJS API Conventions

## Module structure
Every feature module has: `*.module.ts`, `*.controller.ts`, `*.service.ts`, optional `dto/`, optional `*.guard.ts`. Register in `app.module.ts`.

## Auth guards
```typescript
// Always use both guards together for authenticated endpoints
@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard)
@Roles(UserRole.BUSINESS_ADMIN)
@Get()
findAll(@CurrentUser() user: JwtPayload) { ... }
```

## Multi-tenancy — mandatory
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS filter by businessId from the authenticated user
const items = await this.prisma.appointment.findMany({
  where: { businessId: user.businessId },
});

// ❌ NEVER accept businessId from request body/params without validation
```

## Prisma service
Inject `PrismaService` directly — no repository pattern.
```typescript
constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}
```

## DTOs
Use `class-validator` decorators. Validate with `ValidationPipe` (global in `main.ts`).
```typescript
export class CreateAppointmentDto {
  @IsUUID() serviceId: string;
  @IsDateString() startAt: string;
}
```

## Error handling
```typescript
// ✅ Throw NestJS HTTP exceptions
throw new NotFoundException(`Service ${id} not found`);
throw new ForbiddenException('Cannot access another tenant\'s data');

// ❌ Never swallow errors silently
try { ... } catch (e) { /* empty */ }
```

## Pricing / money
Store all monetary values as **integer cents** (`priceCents`, `amountCents`). Never use floats for money.

## Seed
`apps/api/prisma/seed.ts` — upsert-safe. Run: `npm run db:seed` from `apps/api/`.
Seeds: categories, super admin, demo business, 38 SiteContent keys (landing EN+HI, SEO, WA templates, city pages, onboarding).

## Redis injection
Modules that need Redis or BullMQ queues must import `QueuesModule`:
```typescript
@Module({ imports: [QueuesModule], ... })
```
Inject with `@Inject('REDIS')`, `@Inject('QUEUE_WHATSAPP')`, `@Inject('QUEUE_REMINDERS')`.

## Rate limiting
Global `ThrottlerGuard` is already applied as `APP_GUARD`. Per-endpoint override:
```typescript
@Throttle({ default: { ttl: 60_000, limit: 10 } })
@Post('login')
login() { ... }
```

## SiteContent
To read dynamic content in a service or processor, query `prisma.siteContent.findUnique({ where: { key_locale: { key, locale } } })`.
Do NOT hardcode message template strings — always fetch from SiteContent so Super Admin can edit without redeploy.
